**[1853, 12-19] Ms.A.1.2.23.115**

Stowe to WLG; Cabin

Met Douglass and was more favorably impressed than she thought she would
be after her talk with Garrison. “There did not appear to be any deep
underlying stratum of bitterness—he did not seem to me malignant or
revengeful. … You speak of him as an apostate—I cannot but regard this
language as unjustly severe.” Hopes Garrison will alter his opinion of
him.


